transaction_analysis.analysis_summary:
This Commonwealth Bank Viridian Line of Credit statement shows a 3-month period from January 1 to March 31, 2025, for joint account holders Ben and Evelyn Greenway. The account started with a credit balance of $3,120.86 but ended with a significant debit balance of $17,219.26, representing a negative swing of over $20,000.
Key financial patterns include regular salary income of $4,715.06 from Australian Investment Exchange (appearing 3 times), regular Medicare benefit payments totaling $1,718.74, and substantial transfers from family members totaling $9,700. However, outflows significantly exceeded inflows.
Major outflows included frequent transfers to account xx2868 totaling $24,305.45, large purchases at Harvey Norman and Domayne totaling $5,897, a significant $5,000 transfer to Nick Ward, and various family transfers to Revolut accounts. The account also shows regular bill payments for education ($651.88), health insurance ($364.24), utilities, and loan repayments.
The account crossed from credit to debit on February 10, 2025, and the balance deteriorated rapidly in late February/early March due to large retail purchases and continued high outflows. Interest charges of $13.88 were applied in March. The account operates within a $30,000 credit limit with variable interest rates of 8.13-8.38% for balances within the limit.
